Doing a deep dive into how we’re outfitting work stations at Arya, and need some input! We currently have sit/stand desks spec’d that are similar to the (grey top developer) sit/stands here at EBCC. We’ll be reusing our grey + black Knoll chairs, though I noticed y’all use your stations in very individual ways [some sitting at lower level, some standing full-time, mix of both, or some that sit at the standing height!] Plz vote with emojis what you’ll be more inclined to use.  :man_in_business_suit_levitating: = METAL STOOL, :seat: = KNOLL SITTING HEIGHT CHAIR

disclaimer: our default will be outfitting each station with a Knoll chair + a sit/stand desk. a vote will not lock you in to one or the other, though it will help with our ordering of items for our move to 811! any questions? ping me privately + we can chat!! THANK YOU :confetti_ball:

attachments.title: UPDATE: TriMet Could Potentially Interrupt Downtown Core Service During Tomorrow's Protests—Plan Accordingly!
attachments.text: TriMet has announced they will temporarily stop downtown core service of the MAX and bus lines [see update below] during tomorrow afternoon's scheduled Inauguration Day protest, citing "safety concerns." As you probably recall following Trump's election, protesters took to the streets in great numbers and some blocked the passage of MAX trains downtown. In a probable response to this, TriMet is temporarily suspending service in the downtown corridor, specifically around the Pioneer Courthouse Square area—though...
